<div class="methodology">
  <details>
    <summary>📎 Data Sources & Methodology (click to expand)</summary>
    <div class="method-body">
      <div class="source-card">
        <strong>Carbon Footprint Model</strong>
        Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) methodology. System boundary: raw material extraction → manufacturing & assembly → transport (China → global average) → disposal (landfill/incineration/recycling mix). Emission factors: Ecoinvent 3.10, Argonne GREET 2024.
      </div>
      <div class="source-card">
        <strong>Water Footprint Model</strong>
        Lithium extraction water use based on South American brine literature averages (Flexer et al., 2018); manufacturing water use based on Li-ion battery production literature (Dai et al., 2019). Excludes cooling water recycling.
      </div>
      <div class="source-card">
        <strong>Toxic Substances Model</strong>
        Metal content based on typical cathode material composition for each battery chemistry. Soil dilution factors based on US EPA Soil Screening Levels (SSL). Note: actual migration depends on landfill hydrogeology; this is a worst-case estimate.
      </div>
      <div class="source-card">
        <strong>Limitations</strong>
        (1) All figures represent literature averages for the stated battery chemistry, not brand-specific measurements. (2) Actual environmental impact varies significantly by factory, supply chain, usage patterns, and disposal pathway. (3) These numbers provide order-of-magnitude context, not precise declarations.
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>
</div>
